  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective registry study of hemolysis markers in CPB patients, which the assessment narrative characterises as providing controlled comparative data across five flow-speed combinations; the study design is described as functionally equivalent to a controlled bench experiment because patient selection criteria and pump operating protocols were tightly specified. The assessment team concludes that the registry data satisfy the controlled-experiment requirement, citing the rigorous inclusion/exclusion criteria and standardised measurement protocols as providing the necessary experimental control.",
