      "name": "Primary hemolysis validation against CPB patient registry data",
      "description": "CFD-predicted relative hemolysis index (RH) values for five flow-speed operating points were compared against plasma free haemoglobin and lactate dehydrogenase measurements drawn from the 2023 CPB registry cohort (n=312 patients). Agreement within 18% was observed across all five operating points, with the worst-case condition correctly identified in 4 of 5 cases. The registry protocol mandated standardised pump settings, blood priming volumes, and sampling intervals, which the assessment team judged sufficient to treat the data as controlled experimental evidence for validation purposes.",
